1
00:00:06,070 --> 00:00:08,650
I'm going to make an absurd suggestion,
but hear me out, okay?

2
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:15,030
Can I have sex with other individuals?

3
00:00:23,840 --> 00:00:25,340
What?

4
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:30,970
You, having sex...

5
00:00:32,620 --> 00:00:34,290
With other men?

6
00:00:34,290 --> 00:00:35,930
Even though we're married?

7
00:00:35,930 --> 00:00:39,600
- What?
- No, let me explain.

8
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:42,210
It's apparently a thing overseas, and...

9
00:00:42,210 --> 00:00:47,060
You must think it's so funny I have ED.

10
00:00:47,060 --> 00:00:50,280
No, not at all.

11
00:00:50,280 --> 00:00:52,160
Ouji, please listen to me. I...

12
00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:57,960
This is serious to me.
But clearly you don't agree.

13
00:02:07,670 --> 00:02:11,730
[Episode 7]

14
00:02:12,790 --> 00:02:16,200
You sure we don't need to report him?

15
00:02:25,230 --> 00:02:27,860
It's fine. I won't see him again.

16
00:02:31,340 --> 00:02:36,770
I'm partly to blame for aggravating him.

17
00:02:36,770 --> 00:02:41,060
How? You didn't do anything wrong.

18
00:02:46,260 --> 00:02:51,280
Help me forget the bad experience.

19
00:02:52,590 --> 00:02:59,850
Why don't we stay like this for the night?

20
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:11,080
I want you to touch me.

21
00:03:12,650 --> 00:03:14,160
Please?

22
00:03:17,140 --> 00:03:18,840
As you wish.

23
00:03:33,150 --> 00:03:34,880
[Ouji]

24
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:37,900
[Where are you?]
[I'm calling]

25
00:03:39,370 --> 00:03:41,640
He's left me on read.

26
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:44,400
For two weeks now.

27
00:03:48,470 --> 00:03:52,450
Why did I say that?

28
00:03:52,450 --> 00:03:57,120
Why did I think that was such a bright idea?

29
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:59,330
[Kato Publishing]

30
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:14,140
What's up?

31
00:04:16,030 --> 00:04:21,500
One of my steady gigs
is ending our contract this month.

32
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:28,170
They're re-assessing their whole magazine,
or so I was told.

33
00:04:29,270 --> 00:04:31,450
I see.

34
00:04:31,450 --> 00:04:34,260
Nothing you can do about that.

35
00:04:34,260 --> 00:04:35,740
I know.

36
00:04:35,740 --> 00:04:42,400
But it's made me face an unfortunate truth.

37
00:04:43,390 --> 00:04:47,560
- Huh?
- I now have zero steady gigs.

38
00:04:51,780 --> 00:04:53,770
That's, well...

39
00:04:53,770 --> 00:04:57,780
Don't bother cheering me up. I know it's bad.

40
00:04:57,780 --> 00:05:02,630
It's an inevitable for freelancers.

41
00:05:02,630 --> 00:05:05,550
But with your reputation,
work will come your way.

42
00:05:05,550 --> 00:05:08,710
For now, focus on your one-time gigs, and...

43
00:05:11,420 --> 00:05:13,670
Wait... None of those, either?

44
00:05:13,670 --> 00:05:17,350
Yeah. I know I'm screwed.

45
00:05:17,350 --> 00:05:19,850
I'm practically getting by on part-time jobs.

46
00:05:19,850 --> 00:05:23,780
No, not even. I'm not making a single yen.

47
00:05:23,780 --> 00:05:26,560
If I'm not a freelancer, what am I?

48
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,550
A vagrant?

49
00:05:28,550 --> 00:05:32,540
Oh, I am so screwed...

50
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:36,540
At least your husband will support you!

51
00:05:38,690 --> 00:05:40,250
Haru?

52
00:05:42,110 --> 00:05:48,220
Okay. Have you ever had a bright idea that,

53
00:05:48,220 --> 00:05:52,770
when executing it, didn't go well at all?

54
00:05:52,770 --> 00:05:54,750
- Huh?
- An idea so bright,

55
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:57,500
that it clears up the fog in your brain.

56
00:05:57,500 --> 00:06:02,280
Except, when you put it to action...

57
00:06:02,280 --> 00:06:05,250
<i>You must think it's so funny I have ED.</i>

58
00:06:07,230 --> 00:06:09,610
Is this about a project of yours?

59
00:06:09,610 --> 00:06:12,460
Yes. You could say that.

60
00:06:13,210 --> 00:06:17,550
It happens all the time with graphic design.

61
00:06:17,550 --> 00:06:22,910
Clients will shoot down ideas
I think are great.

62
00:06:22,910 --> 00:06:25,530
I see.

63
00:06:25,530 --> 00:06:29,570
Ultimately, it comes down to conversation,

64
00:06:29,570 --> 00:06:34,480
and reconciling our ideas
to create the final product.

65
00:06:36,210 --> 00:06:42,060
Reconciling is important, that's for sure.

66
00:06:42,060 --> 00:06:43,740
[Ouji]

67
00:06:43,740 --> 00:06:46,800
[Where are you?]
[I'm calling]

68
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:55,020
[Touto Publishing]

69
00:06:56,910 --> 00:07:01,940
Do you know Mukai, of Touto Publishing?

70
00:07:01,940 --> 00:07:06,240
She was looking for a new columnist
to write a women's piece.

71
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:10,310
- Really?
- Why not give it a shot?

72
00:07:10,310 --> 00:07:12,550
Okay.

73
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:26,680
Aizawa! Long time no see!

74
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,760
Likewise, Ms. Kotani.

75
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:32,820
Sorry, I guess you're an "Ouji" now.

76
00:07:32,820 --> 00:07:34,280
Indeed.

77
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:37,240
Congratulations on your marriage.

78
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:38,810
Thank you.

79
00:07:38,810 --> 00:07:43,170
To think you'd marry him.
The power of a fan is something else.

80
00:07:43,170 --> 00:07:45,100
I wouldn't say that.

81
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:47,640
Sensei, the car.

82
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:48,800
Thanks.

83
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:50,550
"Sensei"?

84
00:07:50,550 --> 00:07:54,280
A book I released became a hit,
embarrassing as that is to admit.

85
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:56,800
I see.

86
00:07:58,550 --> 00:08:00,960
I hope you enjoyed the curry.

87
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:02,360
Huh?

88
00:08:06,630 --> 00:08:08,600
Curry?

89
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:13,180
<i>I saw the recipe on my friend's account.</i>

90
00:08:19,010 --> 00:08:21,440
[keiko^kotani]

91
00:08:43,140 --> 00:08:45,900
'Sup.

92
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,160
Run away from home?

93
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:51,200
No. Just thought I'd take work seriously.

94
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:53,060
- Really.
- 'Sup.

95
00:08:53,060 --> 00:08:55,790
- Run away from home?
- I said, no!

96
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:59,090
Why're you so prickly
when the band's back together?

97
00:08:59,090 --> 00:09:00,650
I am not prickly.

98
00:09:00,650 --> 00:09:03,420
Here's a gift to lift your spirits.

99
00:09:03,420 --> 00:09:06,450
- What's this?
- Keiko's new book. I bumped into her,

100
00:09:06,450 --> 00:09:10,360
and she gave us each a signed copy.
[I had fun! XXX - Keiko]

101
00:09:13,830 --> 00:09:16,610
What "fun"?

102
00:09:16,610 --> 00:09:18,590
You met up with her?

103
00:09:22,810 --> 00:09:25,040
He's cheating on you?

104
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:29,370
Hold on. I'm not following.

105
00:09:29,370 --> 00:09:34,950
Last I heard, Ouji lacked the drive,
but he hugged you, right?

106
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:40,610
It's not that he lacks it,
it's that he physically can't.

107
00:09:40,610 --> 00:09:42,380
Physically can't?

108
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:48,090
Ah, I see.

109
00:09:48,870 --> 00:09:52,180
Which led them to the brink of a divorce.

110
00:09:53,180 --> 00:09:56,530
This is too much information to handle.

111
00:09:56,530 --> 00:09:59,510
So, why do you suspect him of cheating?

112
00:10:03,380 --> 00:10:05,100
This.

113
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:07,790
Curry?

114
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:14,070
It's the same exact dish Ouji made for me.

115
00:10:14,070 --> 00:10:18,130
Is it?

116
00:10:18,130 --> 00:10:20,380
I mean...

117
00:10:20,380 --> 00:10:21,930
Look.

118
00:10:21,930 --> 00:10:24,790
"#LeftoversCurry".

119
00:10:24,790 --> 00:10:26,910
I can see why that'd get you.

120
00:10:26,910 --> 00:10:29,840
Transforming leftovers into a meal?
She's practically showing off.

121
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:33,370
- But...
- See the canned mackerel she used?

122
00:10:33,940 --> 00:10:37,170
Maybe?

123
00:10:37,170 --> 00:10:40,240
Canned foods aren't "leftovers".

124
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:42,370
They're made to last decades.

125
00:10:42,370 --> 00:10:43,940
Fair point.

126
00:10:43,940 --> 00:10:50,560
It was in our curry, too.
He went and bought a can, for this.

127
00:10:50,560 --> 00:10:52,200
I see.

128
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:56,610
- Even so, that's no reason to...
- Haru.

129
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:03,150
I might've seen it.

130
00:11:03,150 --> 00:11:04,990
Seen, what?

131
00:11:14,290 --> 00:11:17,160
Sorry, I couldn't find the time to tell you.

132
00:11:17,160 --> 00:11:20,530
You can't see their faces.

133
00:11:20,530 --> 00:11:23,040
- That's clearly Ouji.
- Maybe, but the woman...

134
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:26,120
- They came out, together!
- She may not be Kotani.

135
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,800
When?

136
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:32,630
About a month ago.

137
00:11:37,740 --> 00:11:40,020
- We're taking a quick break.
- Sure.

138
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:46,540
[Haru: 10 Unread Messages]

139
00:11:46,540 --> 00:11:49,370
[Haru: We have to talk]
[I'll be waiting at home]

140
00:11:57,300 --> 00:11:59,170
I'm home.

141
00:12:05,210 --> 00:12:08,110
What do you mean, "talk"?

142
00:12:15,910 --> 00:12:17,840
Haruchan?

143
00:12:21,130 --> 00:12:23,590
Why the nickname?

144
00:12:23,590 --> 00:12:27,010
Huh? What are you talking about?

145
00:12:29,010 --> 00:12:34,130
You asked her for the curry recipe.

146
00:12:34,130 --> 00:12:35,800
Curry?

147
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:40,440
[keiko^kotani]

148
00:12:46,850 --> 00:12:50,090
No, her post coincidentally appeared
on my timeline.

149
00:12:50,090 --> 00:12:52,210
I was thinking it looked good,

150
00:12:52,210 --> 00:12:56,450
when she happened to DM me,
so I asked for the recipe.

151
00:12:57,200 --> 00:13:00,580
She "happened" to DM you?

152
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:03,720
Sounds mighty convenient.

153
00:13:03,720 --> 00:13:05,520
What are you...

154
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:09,910
A text from your
longest lasting girlfriend of two years.

155
00:13:09,910 --> 00:13:11,750
What sort of metric is that?

156
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:13,120
You kept in touch with her?

157
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:16,820
I'm telling you, it was a coincidence.

158
00:13:16,820 --> 00:13:20,400
Then was November 13th also a "coincidence"?

159
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:21,880
What?

160
00:13:31,940 --> 00:13:34,240
Why?

161
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:36,330
No, we weren't...

162
00:13:36,330 --> 00:13:38,790
And where'd you get this photo?

163
00:13:40,390 --> 00:13:42,200
Did you do it with her?

164
00:13:42,850 --> 00:13:45,560
You can't with me, but with your ex?

165
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:49,110
- Like I said...
- Guess I can't beat two years of history.

166
00:13:49,110 --> 00:13:51,740
I was only ever a fan in the background.

167
00:13:51,740 --> 00:13:53,980
We got married because it was easy for you.

168
00:13:53,980 --> 00:13:56,410
- Is that why...
- Knock it off already!

169
00:13:59,940 --> 00:14:02,980
You don't trust a thing I said?

170
00:14:04,110 --> 00:14:06,020
Well...

171
00:14:16,090 --> 00:14:17,710
Fine.

172
00:14:18,530 --> 00:14:20,530
Do what you want.

173
00:14:23,430 --> 00:14:28,850
Doubt me, have sex with other men. Whatever.

174
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:33,950
<i>Those eyes.</i>

175
00:14:34,510 --> 00:14:37,850
- <i>Ouji...</i>
- <i>You're a bit too persistent.</i>

176
00:14:37,850 --> 00:14:42,270
<i>Those cold eyes of his always shut me up.</i>

177
00:14:42,270 --> 00:14:45,620
<i>This is serious to me.</i>

178
00:14:45,620 --> 00:14:51,400
<i>I'd rather put aside my own desires,
than have this person hate me.</i>

179
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:57,170
NOT!

180
00:15:01,190 --> 00:15:02,780
Fine.

181
00:15:02,780 --> 00:15:06,560
I will do what I want. Whatever I want.

182
00:15:25,980 --> 00:15:30,230
But what is it I want?

183
00:15:30,230 --> 00:15:32,540
Did you say something just now?

184
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:40,380
Let's just say being given sudden free reign

185
00:15:40,380 --> 00:15:44,200
is difficult to deal with in its own right.

186
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:46,250
Your project was approved?

187
00:15:46,250 --> 00:15:48,360
Huh?

188
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:51,280
Was this not about your proposal
to Touto Publishing?

189
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:54,060
I was hoping it went well...

190
00:15:54,060 --> 00:15:56,250
Yeah, that's what I was talking about.

191
00:15:56,250 --> 00:15:59,790
I'm just... waiting to hear back from them.

192
00:15:59,790 --> 00:16:03,190
I'm glad things are going
in a positive direction.

193
00:16:22,780 --> 00:16:24,740
Hello?

194
00:16:27,020 --> 00:16:29,150
Sorry I kept you.

195
00:16:29,150 --> 00:16:33,030
You don't usually initiate the invite.
What's up?

196
00:16:33,030 --> 00:16:37,700
Well, I do feel partly responsible
for what happened, so...

197
00:16:40,770 --> 00:16:43,260
You left the house?

198
00:16:43,260 --> 00:16:46,550
Yeah. It's been three days since I left,

199
00:16:46,550 --> 00:16:49,070
and I've been reading all the manga I want.

200
00:16:49,070 --> 00:16:51,010
You're staying at a manga cafe?

201
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:53,810
Go to a hotel, you're not a broke student.

202
00:16:53,810 --> 00:16:55,820
Well, I am a vagrant right now.

203
00:16:55,820 --> 00:16:57,010
A vagrant?

204
00:16:57,010 --> 00:16:59,500
Never mind.

205
00:17:05,940 --> 00:17:09,050
Fuyumi says she'll be here soon.

206
00:17:09,050 --> 00:17:10,570
But what about Chizuka?

207
00:17:10,570 --> 00:17:13,620
She's apparently making up
for a canceled sleepover.

208
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:28,580
Sorry I'm late!

209
00:17:28,580 --> 00:17:30,900
Fuyumi!

210
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:34,200
- Drunk already?
- Yeah, she's going fast today.

211
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:36,840
So? What happened?

212
00:17:38,380 --> 00:17:42,300
- Your lamb chops. Enjoy.
- Thank you.

213
00:17:42,300 --> 00:17:44,220
I see. Ouji got mad at you.

214
00:17:44,220 --> 00:17:47,820
He did! I don't understand why.

215
00:17:47,820 --> 00:17:49,530
I'm the one should be mad!

216
00:17:49,530 --> 00:17:51,950
- So you got mad back.
- Yup.

217
00:17:51,950 --> 00:17:56,960
Except, now you don't know what to do.

218
00:17:58,840 --> 00:18:01,650
Why not have sex with another dude?

219
00:18:01,650 --> 00:18:06,770
Ouji gave you his explicit permission.

220
00:18:06,770 --> 00:18:12,160
Yeah. But that's only because I asked first.

221
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:16,580
No, I asked before his affair, not after it!

222
00:18:16,580 --> 00:18:18,440
B-Before his affair?

223
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:22,160
So you weren't talking about revenge sex?

224
00:18:22,920 --> 00:18:27,540
Ouji said if we couldn't have sex,
then we shouldn't stay together.

225
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:32,140
I want to stay with him.
But never having sex, is a bit...

226
00:18:32,140 --> 00:18:34,670
So you suggested other partners?

227
00:18:34,670 --> 00:18:39,050
It's apparently a thing overseas,
so I blurted it out.

228
00:18:39,050 --> 00:18:40,830
And how did Ouji react?

229
00:18:40,830 --> 00:18:42,680
- He completely lost his cool.
- I see.

230
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:46,700
Yet he makes his own affair an exception?

231
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:48,770
That's why I blew a fuse, too.

232
00:18:48,770 --> 00:18:51,100
Make sense.

233
00:18:51,940 --> 00:18:54,940
I'll introduce you to someone.

234
00:18:54,940 --> 00:18:57,100
- Huh?
- The perfect man for you.

235
00:18:57,100 --> 00:18:59,920
- Akina.
- A professional, with no strings attached.

236
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:02,180
- A professional?
- Oh!

237
00:19:02,180 --> 00:19:05,290
The people from the male brothel?

238
00:19:05,290 --> 00:19:07,590
Sorry, who?

239
00:19:07,590 --> 00:19:09,780
I guess I haven't told you yet.

240
00:19:09,780 --> 00:19:13,760
I'm currently in love with my therapist
from a male brothel.

241
00:19:15,420 --> 00:19:19,240
So there are male brothels.

242
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:20,920
That's the part that shocks you?

243
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:23,940
I'm just a bit overwhelmed with information.

244
00:19:23,940 --> 00:19:26,540
How about the three of us all call someone?

245
00:19:26,540 --> 00:19:29,140
They can come chill, nothing steamy involved.

246
00:19:29,140 --> 00:19:32,160
Jumping in solo is a bit much for you, right?

247
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:35,450
Yes, but Fuyumi wouldn't...

248
00:19:35,450 --> 00:19:37,710
Married women call on them, too.

249
00:19:37,710 --> 00:19:40,920
- They do?
- Yeah. To alleviate their stress.

250
00:19:45,180 --> 00:19:50,560
But you don't have any stress
to alleviate, do you?

251
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:53,040
- My bad.
- Exactly.

252
00:19:53,040 --> 00:19:56,180
Fuyumi's the only one of us
leading a respectable, happy lifestyle.

253
00:19:56,180 --> 00:19:58,640
Hey, I lead a respectable lifestyle, too.

254
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:03,460
It's not respectable at all.

255
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:09,100
Ouch, that hurts.

256
00:20:09,100 --> 00:20:12,180
- I was referring to myself.
- Huh?

257
00:20:13,440 --> 00:20:17,940
My husband only acts like
he understands my work.

258
00:20:17,940 --> 00:20:19,970
He harasses me to "do better".

259
00:20:24,550 --> 00:20:25,980
I'm sorry.

260
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:28,930
Can I fess up about something?

261
00:20:30,190 --> 00:20:36,360
Remember that coworker I mentioned
who was having an affair with an actor?

262
00:20:37,100 --> 00:20:39,020
That was actually me.

263
00:20:40,230 --> 00:20:42,410
- What?
- Y-You're so cool!

264
00:20:42,410 --> 00:20:44,050
I'm not "cool" at all.

265
00:20:44,050 --> 00:20:46,160
Sorry, I couldn't help myself.

266
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:49,940
- How long?
- About half a year now.

267
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:56,630
I spoke big to you, Haru. But the truth is...

268
00:20:56,630 --> 00:21:03,950
<i>First, you have to accept
your true feelings and desires.</i>

269
00:21:05,310 --> 00:21:09,970
<i>Don't worry. Accept yourself,
and you'll feel a whole lot better.</i>

270
00:21:10,610 --> 00:21:14,500
I was talking about my own experiences.

271
00:21:15,480 --> 00:21:19,080
I had no confidence in myself,

272
00:21:19,080 --> 00:21:22,980
and would always worry alone.

273
00:21:24,820 --> 00:21:30,720
But things became easier
when I began seeing him.

274
00:21:32,740 --> 00:21:36,730
It was like I was affirming my own existence.

275
00:21:37,550 --> 00:21:40,760
Affirming yourself.

276
00:21:42,360 --> 00:21:46,840
But that's no reason to look highly of me.

277
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:50,350
Just the other day, I faced a definite risk.

278
00:21:50,350 --> 00:21:54,250
- Did your husband find out?
- No, but it got close.

279
00:21:57,180 --> 00:21:59,610
That's the end of my confession.

280
00:21:59,610 --> 00:22:02,110
Aw, I want to hear more!

281
00:22:02,110 --> 00:22:03,600
- Next time.
- No, now.

282
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:06,640
We're not here for my story, remember?

283
00:22:09,810 --> 00:22:13,640
So? What'll it be, Haru?

284
00:22:14,670 --> 00:22:16,080
Huh?

285
00:22:16,080 --> 00:22:21,190
Want to be a bit adventurous?

286
00:22:43,850 --> 00:22:46,880
Akina, actually...

287
00:22:56,510 --> 00:22:58,040
Good evening.

288
00:22:58,700 --> 00:23:00,810
We're with the Ebisu Boys Club.

289
00:23:00,810 --> 00:23:02,460
Come on in.

290
00:23:57,700 --> 00:24:01,180
<i>My adventure has begun.</i>

291
00:24:40,970 --> 00:24:49,020
[Preview]
